# CTEQ6/  --  Fortran PDF library
#
# Files that belong in this directory:
#
#   Cteq6Pdf-2007.f   Fortran source (v6.52, April 2007)
#   cteq6m.tbl        CTEQ6M  NLO MSbar  iset=1  <-- Fortran default
#   cteq6d.tbl        CTEQ6D  NLO DIS    iset=2
#   cteq6l.tbl        CTEQ6L  LO         iset=3
#   cteq6l1.tbl       CTEQ6L1 LO (alphaS fitted)  iset=4
#
# All four files above are present in this distribution.
#
# ISET MAPPING (from the source comments in Cteq6Pdf-2007.f)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
#  Iset  PDF set   Scheme    alphaS(Mz)   Table file
#  ----  --------  --------  ----------   -----------
#   1    CTEQ6M    MSbar     0.118        cteq6m.tbl  <- used by original Fortran
#   2    CTEQ6D    DIS       0.118        cteq6d.tbl
#   3    CTEQ6L    LO        0.118        cteq6l.tbl
#   4    CTEQ6L1   LO        0.130        cteq6l1.tbl
#
# The original Fortran (3Var_x.f, f2_pi_sub.f90) calls:
#   CALL SETCTQ6(1)   ! CTEQ 'MS-bar' SCHEME
# so iset=1 (CTEQ6M, NLO) is the default in this C++ code too.
#
# RUNTIME NOTE
# ------------
# SetCtq6 opens the table file by name in the working directory:
#   Open(IU, File='cteq6m.tbl', Status='OLD', ...)
# CMake copies the .tbl files to the build directory at configure
# time, so running the executable from the build directory works.
# If you run from another directory, symlink or copy the .tbl
# files next to the executable.
#
# BUILD
# -----
#   cmake -B build -DUSE_CTEQ6=ON
#   cmake --build build
#
# PRECISION NOTE
# --------------
# Cteq6Pdf-2007.f uses "Implicit REAL" (4-byte single precision).
# The C++ wrapper in include/CTEQ6.hh handles all float<->double
# casts internally.
#
# COMPILER NAME MANGLING
# ----------------------
# gfortran appends a trailing underscore: SetCtq6 -> setctq6_
# This matches the extern "C" declarations in include/CTEQ6.hh.
# ifort uses the same convention by default.
# flang: same. If you see linker errors, check with:
#   nm libPionCloudLib.a | grep -i ctq
